title: Laboratory in Educational Research and Outreach
description: This course provides experience conducting educational research and outreach for children in greater San Diego County. May be taken for credit three times. Open to the following majors only: PC26, PC28, PC29, PC30, PC31, PC32, PC33, PC34, CG32. Prerequisites: upper-division standing, PSYC 60 or COGS 14B and PSYC 70 or COGS 14A. Instructor approval.
